I"\<p>I got a toy piano at the age four, and I’ve been a band geek ever since. I taught myself to play most wind, a few percussion, and a number of string instruments. The instrument I longed for most as a child was a piano. In my working class family home, an oft-heard response to my piano pleads were “pianos are for rich people, Zinzy”. As a young girl, I promised myself that I’d one day buy myself a piano.</p>

<p>On my 35th birthday I gave myself what I promised.</p>

<p>Below you’ll find rough notes of what I’m learning.</p>

