  </li>
  <li>I’m quite pleased with how I’ve set up my piano practice, but it makes me nervous. I’ve fully embraced my learning style (and the hyper focus around which it revolves), yet I know that success on the piano means consistency. I’m running an experiment: I’m surrounding myself with other projects that can spark my hyper focus to accommodate the consistency I need to build.</li>
</ul>
